All schools and district departments will reopen on Tuesday, December 12th on their regular schedules. The winds are diminishing and SDGE has restored power to much of Valley Center with only about 600 customers still without power today, hopefully to be restored tonight. Students do not need to make up the day and are not counted absent for today.
A big thank you to CAL Fire, SD Sheriff's Department and all first responders for keeping Valley Center safe during this unprecedented purple flag warning.

post_text:
After consulting with CAL Fire, and due to large scale power outages that are anticipated to continue through Monday afternoon, we have decided all Valley Center - Pauma schools will be closed on Monday December 11, 2017. We continue to closely monitor weather, power and fire conditions in our area. We are very grateful to the combined efforts of local law enforcement, CAL Fire and all other first responders who are doing an incredible job of keeping us safe.
We will update parents and guardians via parentlink call, our website and social media.
Thank you.

post_text:
Update regarding the law enforcement incident at Lilac School on Wednesday, November 29th. We have been advised by San Diego County Sheriff’s Department that the Sheriff’s department received a report of alleged off-campus criminal activity involving an adult. Out of an abundance of caution, deputies took an adult into custody outside Lilac School yesterday. The allegations were determined to be unfounded, the adult was released and no criminal charges were filed.

We understand that this was a disturbing incident for the students and parents who may have witnessed or heard about this. Parentlink calls in English and Spanish will be made to parents of all Lilac School students today with this information. We will have increased security presence at school and counselors available for students as needed. Student safety continues to be our top priority and we appreciate parents, staff and community in our partnership in our students' education.

post_text:
Update:
Bus 105 was at a complete stop on Circle R Road this morning when a semi truck came in contact with the driver's side mirror and window. CHP and Fire Dept. responded as well as Cheri McGee and Erik Groscup from VCPUSD Transportation. All passengers were evaluated and no injuries were found, all were released. Students were transported to school on a replacement bus. Well done, Valley Center first responders and VCPUSD transportation team! Student safety is our priority and everyone worked together to make sure our students got to school safely.

post_text:
The Valley Center – Pauma Unified School District Board of Trustees is pleased to announce the appointment of Ron McCowan as Superintendent of Schools, effective January 1, 2018.

Mr. McCowan is a longstanding member of the Valley Center – Pauma administrative team with nineteen years as an administrator in the district, serving as Principal of the Elementary Upper School, Vice Principal and Principal of Valley Center High School. Ron holds a Master’s Degree in Educational Leadership from Azusa Pacific University, and is a former high school biology teacher. Ron and his wife Nell Rose live in Valley Center with their three boys, who have attended Valley Center schools from elementary on up through high school.

Mr. McCowan will continue as principal of Valley Center High School through the end of the calendar year and will work closely with Superintendent Mary Gorsuch and staff for a smooth transition at the beginning of the new year.
text:

Ron holds a Master’s Degree in Educational Leadership from Azusa Pacific University, and is a former high school biology teacher. Ron and his wife Nell Rose live in Valley Center with their three boys, who have attended Valley Center schools from elementary on up through high school.

Mr. McCowan will continue as principal of Valley Center High School through the end of the calendar year and will work closely with Superintendent Mary Gorsuch and staff for a smooth transition at the beginning of the new year.

post_text: It's Reality Week at Valley Center High School. Students will participate in activities to teach them about the harsh consequences of drinking and driving. On Wednesday, there will be a mock accident and actual first responders on campus as part of the week's events. Community members may see or hear first responders near campus - this is part of the demonstration and not a real emergency. Many thanks to Mothers Against Drunk Driving and local first responders who are partnering with us in this important work to keep our students safe.

post_text:
Greetings,

This is Superintendent Mary Gorsuch with a message regarding your student’s school records and information. A letter will be sent home with detailed information about a recent California District Court ruling that requires the California Department of Education to release student information to the Morgan Hill Concerned Parents Association. The Valley Center Pauma Unified School District is not named in the lawsuit, and is not releasing any student information to outside parties, but the California Department of Education will be required to do so. Parents have the right to object by sending in a form that will be provided to you as part of the letter we are sending this week. All parents need to do is to complete and return the form to their child’s teacher or school office by March 18th.

Valley Center Pauma goes to great lengths to protect your family’s personal information, and we want to do all we can to help you to keep it protected. If you have any questions, please contact your child’s school principal.

Thank you.
text:
Greetings,

This is Superintendent Mary Gorsuch with a message regarding your student’s school records and information. A letter will be sent home with detailed information about a recent California District Court ruling that requires the California Department of Education to release student information to the Morgan Hill Concerned Parents Association. The Valley Center Pauma Unified School District is not named in the lawsuit, and is not releasing any student information to outside parties, but the California Department of Education will be required to do so. Parents have the right to object by sending in a form that will be provided to you as part of the letter we are sending this week. All parents need to do is to complete and return the form to their child’s teacher or school office by March 18th.

Valley Center Pauma goes to great lengths to protect your family’s personal information, and we want to do all we can to help you to keep it protected. If you have any questions, please contact your child’s school principal.

Thank you.
